ents of Quaternary science in botany, palaeontology, climatology, geology, archaeology, and pedology, this book makes a significant contribution to our understanding of the past and present environments of the Canadian North.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPaleobotanyyQuaternary. 0aPaleobotanyzNorthwest TerritorieszMackenzie River. 0aPaleobotanyzYukon. 0aPlantszNorthwest TerritorieszMackenzie River. 0aPlantszYukon. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Botany.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758035340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487580353423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487580353.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK